quran[21]{c,v,t,f}:
  56,82,"And make [the thanks for] your provision that you deny [the Provider]?"
  56,83,"Then why, when it [i.e., the soul at death] reaches the throat"
  56,84,"And you are at that time looking on -"
  67,22,"Then is one who walks fallen on his face better guided or one who walks erect on a straight path?"
  67,23,"Say, "
  67,24,"Say, "
  68,16,"We will brand him upon the snout.{1}",1:[Literally, "trunk," meaning the nose of an elephant or pig.]
  68,17,"Indeed, We have tried them as We tried the companions of the garden, when they swore to cut its fruit in the [early] morning"
  68,18,"Without making exception.{1}",1:[i.e., without conceding that nothing can be accomplished unless Allāh wills, saying, "...if Allāh wills" ("in-shā’-Allāh").  See 18:23-24.]
  69,13,"Then when the Horn is blown with one blast"
  69,14,"And the earth and the mountains are lifted and leveled with one blow [i.e., stroke] -"
  69,15,"Then on that Day, the Occurrence [i.e., Resurrection] will occur,"
  70,7,"But We see it [as] near."
  70,8,"On the Day the sky will be like murky oil,{1}",1:[Or "molten metal."]
  70,9,"And the mountains will be like wool,{1}",1:[i.e., in the process of disintegration.]
  71,4,"He [i.e., Allāh] will forgive you of your sins and delay you for a specified term. Indeed, the time [set by] Allāh, when it comes, will not be delayed, if you only knew."
  71,5,"He said, "
  71,6,"But my invitation increased them not except in flight [i.e., aversion]."
  72,1,"Say, [O Muḥammad], "
  72,2,"It guides to the right course, and we have believed in it. And we will never associate with our Lord anyone."
  72,3,"And [it teaches] that exalted is the nobleness of our Lord; He has not taken a wife or a son"